1
00:00:02,419 --> 00:00:04,669
("Hark! The Herald Angels Sing"
instrumental playing)

2
00:00:09,175 --> 00:00:11,085
-(dogs barking)
-(sleigh bells jingling)

3
00:00:11,177 --> 00:00:12,137
(grunts)

4
00:00:14,347 --> 00:00:16,347
-(music stops)
-Smithers, release the Christmas hounds.

5
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,353
-(barking)
-(screaming)

6
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:20,475
(growling, barking)

7
00:00:20,562 --> 00:00:23,232
("Hark! The Herald Angels Sing"
resumes playing)

8
00:00:27,944 --> 00:00:30,114
{\an8}<i>SINGERS:</i>
<i>♪ All is not well, on this Noel ♪</i>

9
00:00:30,196 --> 00:00:32,656
{\an8}<i>♪ It's looking grim for Reverend Tim ♪</i>

10
00:00:32,741 --> 00:00:34,781
{\an8}<i>HELEN:</i>
<i>♪ This should be his very busy season ♪</i>

11
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:37,118
{\an8}<i>SIDESHOW MEL: ♪ No one's coming,</i>
<i>tell me what's the reason ♪</i>

12
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,333
{\an8}-(snoring)
<i>-SINGERS: ♪ What will he do? ♪</i>

13
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:39,373
{\an8}<i>♪ Pull up a pew ♪</i>

14
00:00:39,456 --> 00:00:41,706
{\an8}<i>(singing quiets)</i>
<i>♪ As we bid adieu, look for Disco Stu ♪</i>

15
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:49,381
{\an8}Usually, the Fourth Sunday of Advent
is packed.

16
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:51,716
{\an8}I hope the reverend
isn't losing his touch.

17
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:54,221
{\an8}Comparing the Three Wise Men
to the Beastie Boys

18
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:56,604
{\an8}seemed more desperate than hip.
I'm serious.

19
00:00:59,225 --> 00:01:02,435
{\an8}(groans)
Even Milhouse could've made that.

20
00:01:02,520 --> 00:01:03,650
{\an8}What is it, Helen?

21
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,860
{\an8}Uh, well, Tim,
just thought you should know,

22
00:01:05,940 --> 00:01:08,650
{\an8}a very special fan club
is waiting to talk to you.

23
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,855
{\an8}Mm!

24
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:13,913
{\an8}A semi-circle? What gives?

25
00:01:14,949 --> 00:01:16,619
{\an8}Ned? Agnes?

26
00:01:16,701 --> 00:01:18,661
{\an8}Mel? The Parson?

27
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:20,325
{\an8}That's right, your boss.

28
00:01:20,413 --> 00:01:23,713
{\an8}And I'd like to introduce you
to my boss, the Patriarch.

29
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:27,052
{\an8}Actually, Parson,
we all have the same boss.

30
00:01:27,128 --> 00:01:29,088
{\an8}The Metropolitan.

31
00:01:29,172 --> 00:01:32,432
{\an8}And it is his will
that we come together here for...

32
00:01:32,509 --> 00:01:35,349
{\an8}a divine intervention.

33
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:37,178
{\an8}Look, since when is it a crime

34
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:39,473
{\an8}to mix Pinot Noir and Vicodin?

35
00:01:39,557 --> 00:01:43,647
{\an8}Oh, we don't care if you wreck your liver
with Sancerre and acetaminophen.

36
00:01:43,728 --> 00:01:47,858
{\an8}You can pop pain pills
like cran-raisins for all we care.

37
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:51,191
{\an8}We're here 'cause you're not
packing the p-p-p-pews.

38
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:55,157
{\an8}The church is emptier than a syrup bottle
after a pancake breakfast.

39
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:57,740
{\an8}Oh, people have reasons to miss mass.

40
00:01:57,826 --> 00:01:59,076
{\an8}There's flu going around.

41
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,750
{\an8}The new Jeeps are in at the dealership.

42
00:02:00,829 --> 00:02:03,869
{\an8}Lot of new features,
the big screen up front, where...

43
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:05,747
{\an8}It's not just attendance, Reverend.

44
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:08,554
It's that sometimes when you speak,
my mind wanders,

45
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:11,878
to, uh, non-religious areas.

46
00:02:14,384 --> 00:02:16,644
Timothy, admit it. You're in a slump.

47
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:20,469
How many souls have you personally
converted to our faith this year?

48
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:21,887
Negative six.

49
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:24,305
You have some converting to do.

50
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:26,604
(groaning)

51
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:28,858
I haven't been heard from!

52
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,570
And what do you have to say?

53
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:33,700
Nothing! Just pointing it out.

54
00:02:33,778 --> 00:02:35,948
Okay, I can do this.

55
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,410
I'm a good man.

56
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:41,040
And Springfield is nothing
if not a good Christian community.

57
00:02:41,119 --> 00:02:42,869
♪ ♪

58
00:02:45,957 --> 00:02:47,877
(cries out)

59
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:49,209
(laughing)

60
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:51,594
(grumbles)
I'm worried about this festival.

61
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:54,221
It's like something you'd see
in a college town.

62
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:57,139
Come on, Mom,
get with the pagan agenda.

63
00:02:57,218 --> 00:03:00,098
Ha. This doggy likes me.

64
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:03,430
Don't worry, Ralphie,
I'll shoot you off of there.

65
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:04,386
Uh-oh.

66
00:03:04,475 --> 00:03:07,645
Come on, guys, let's go check out
this year's feature attraction--

67
00:03:07,729 --> 00:03:09,939
the Strandbeest.

68
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:12,073
Powered by the wind!

69
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:16,150
Wow.
Uh... is this science, or garbage?

70
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:18,067
-Dutch art.
-Ooh!

71
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:20,366
And I'll bet
it's environmentally conscious.

72
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:21,830
No. It is not.

73
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,950
{\an8}(onlookers murmuring)

74
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:26,828
Whoa. It's alive!

75
00:03:26,915 --> 00:03:28,875
{\an8}(excited murmuring)

76
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,795
Hmm. The wind is picking up slightly.

77
00:03:32,879 --> 00:03:34,129
This is a disaster!

78
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:36,424
The Beest is built for
the polite breezes of Europe.

79
00:03:36,507 --> 00:03:38,887
(panicked shouting)

80
00:03:38,968 --> 00:03:41,348
-Save me, Odin. (grunts)
-(screaming)

81
00:03:41,429 --> 00:03:43,639
Look, Dad, I can skate backwards!

82
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:47,523
Great, Sophie!
Just watch out for Strandbeests!

83
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:49,152
(laughter)

84
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:50,439
(shocked gasps)

85
00:03:50,521 --> 00:03:51,561
(screaming)

86
00:03:51,648 --> 00:03:53,518
{\an8}(stammering grunts)

87
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,318
{\an8}(grunting)

88
00:03:55,401 --> 00:03:57,491
{\an8}(screams)

89
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:59,070
(grunting)

90
00:03:59,155 --> 00:04:01,155
What the... (grunting)

91
00:04:03,826 --> 00:04:05,196
Okay, I got to warn ya.

92
00:04:05,286 --> 00:04:07,496
Regular morphine
doesn't work on me anymore.

93
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:10,500
Call this number
and they'll send the stuff I need.

94
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,843
It'll say "for elephants,"
but ignore that.

95
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,169
(groans)

96
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:15,844
Sorry about this, Sophie.

97
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:18,172
Couldn't have come at a worse time.

98
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:21,468
I only get one week of custody,
once a year.

99
00:04:21,552 --> 00:04:22,932
It's okay, Dad.

100
00:04:23,012 --> 00:04:25,562
We'll get to know each other
in this semi-private room.

101
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,730
Oh, I'll give you
all the privacy you need.

102
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:29,809
-Ah...
-(flat lines)

103
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:34,151
-(screams) Harold?
-Private room!

104
00:04:35,275 --> 00:04:36,935
Mm-hmm.

105
00:04:38,736 --> 00:04:42,526
Uh... so, uh,
how's your act coming along?

106
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:44,325
I'm not in show business.

107
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:46,369
What kind of a screwed-up kid are you?

108
00:04:46,452 --> 00:04:48,542
I'm not screwed up. I get good grades.

109
00:04:48,621 --> 00:04:50,871
-I play the French horn.
-Good, good.

110
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,827
You know,
it's funny when someone's playing it

111
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,457
and their pants fall down.

112
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:56,594
-(chuckles)
-I haven't had that happen.

113
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,051
Well, don't feel bad.

114
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:00,051
It's actually a pretty complicated rig.

115
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:02,143
The whole megillah is a big tzimmes.

116
00:05:02,218 --> 00:05:04,258
Tzimmes? Megillah?

117
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,425
It's Yiddish.

118
00:05:05,513 --> 00:05:07,893
The language of our <i>fakakta </i>people.

119
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:10,064
Mom raised me Christian.

120
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:12,063
A Christian?

121
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:14,555
(groans)
That <i>farbissina </i>shiksa.

122
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:18,527
How can you ignore the sacred traditions
of the Jewish people?

123
00:05:18,609 --> 00:05:21,899
Krusty, here's your bacon, lobster,
and tref sandwich.

124
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:24,698
Hey, it was supposed to come
with a side of camel.

125
00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:26,122
Extra cloven.

126
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:29,080
Dad, you don't have to be
sort of funny with me.

127
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:32,792
The thing is,
I want to celebrate this time with you.

128
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:34,794
Sweetie, I know you're reaching out.

129
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:38,046
But to me, Christmas is just another day.

130
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:41,669
I usually curl up
with a good bookmaker, and...

131
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:44,972
Well...

132
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:48,473
Why don't the two of you
spend Christmas with us?

133
00:05:48,556 --> 00:05:50,016
Our home isn't fancy,

134
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:53,269
but we'd love to set a place
for two more.

135
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:55,523
Marge, we accept.

136
00:05:55,605 --> 00:05:58,105
-Can we bring anything?
-Just yourself.

137
00:05:58,191 --> 00:05:59,481
That'll cost you.

138
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:02,612
(singsongy) Oh, Maggie.

139
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:04,485
Guess who just came down the chimney?

140
00:06:04,572 --> 00:06:06,452
A magical holiday friend,

141
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:09,162
straight from the North Pole.

142
00:06:09,243 --> 00:06:12,253
He's called the Gnome In Your Home,
and he works for Santa,

143
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:14,790
by watching you all the time.

144
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:17,963
According to a book sold separately,

145
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,764
the Gnome In Your Home
doesn't need food or sleep.

146
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:23,588
He lives for just one thing--

147
00:06:23,674 --> 00:06:26,554
to tell Santa if you're bad or good.

148
00:06:26,636 --> 00:06:27,756
(sucking pacifier rapidly)

149
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:31,845
He's gonna live here on your shelf,
and he never shuts his eyes.

150
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,143
Isn't that cute?

151
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:37,476
You'd better be good,
or he'll nibble your wittle fingers!

152
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:39,483
(sucking pacifier rapidly)

153
00:06:39,565 --> 00:06:41,565
(playing "O Tannenbaum" on piano)

154
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:50,704
-(doorbell rings)
-Oh, boy, Krusty's here!

155
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:54,662
A very merry Christmas,

156
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:57,327
from the bottom of my heart.

157
00:06:57,417 --> 00:06:59,287
(calling) Did you get the shot?

158
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:01,337
How did it play? Was I too sincere?

159
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:04,471
-Perfect, Mr. K!
-Start laying dolly track.

160
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:05,839
{\an8}("Jingle Bells" playing)

161
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:07,762
{\an8}(doorbell rings)

162
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:10,513
{\an8}Come on, damn it!

163
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:14,176
{\an8}Christmas is about one thing--
being with family.

164
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:17,017
{\an8}Sophie, come sit on Daddy's lap.

165
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,863
I don't want to be on camera.

166
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:21,518
Fine, we'll just
motion-capture her in later.

167
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:25,243
{\an8}(screeching)

168
00:07:27,155 --> 00:07:29,485
{\an8}Aw, that's my girl.

169
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:32,744
{\an8}Oh, what a beautiful gingerbread house.

170
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:34,367
{\an8}Wish I could make one.

171
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:38,294
{\an8}And I can!
On a multi-function Minolta printer.

172
00:07:38,374 --> 00:07:40,384
{\an8}Print, scan, copy,

173
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:43,420
{\an8}let Minolta do your Xeroxing!

174
00:07:43,504 --> 00:07:47,054
{\an8}"...when what to my wondering
eyes did appear..."

175
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:49,053
{\an8}To hear me read the rest of this poem,

176
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,385
{\an8}dial 1-900-OLD-POEM.

177
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:53,061
{\an8}$9.95 per call.

178
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:55,559
{\an8}All I wanted was to spend
the holidays with you

179
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:57,731
{\an8}so we could learn more about each other.

180
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,600
{\an8}Well, I learned!

181
00:07:59,687 --> 00:08:00,937
{\an8}Get out!

182
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:03,902
{\an8}-(crying)
-What? Seriously?

183
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:06,443
{\an8}You really want me to go?

184
00:08:06,527 --> 00:08:08,277
{\an8}Yes.

185
00:08:08,362 --> 00:08:09,992
{\an8}Right now.

186
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,575
(doorbell rings)

187
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:17,080
Uh, can we get some room tone?

188
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:19,293
Just 20 seconds.

189
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:34,684
Oh, Sophie! Please, forgive me.

190
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:36,274
I canceled the show.

191
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:38,599
I'm pulling up duct tape myself,

192
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:41,274
like a caveman!

193
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:43,944
SOPHIE:
(crying) Just leave me alone.

194
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:46,653
(groaning)

195
00:08:47,818 --> 00:08:50,068
{\an8}If the Word of God isn't enough,

196
00:08:50,154 --> 00:08:52,994
{\an8}I also have some rubber jar openers.

197
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:56,164
(groans) I've been directing
Christmas pageants for 30 years.

198
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:58,664
There's no way there's a God.

199
00:08:58,746 --> 00:09:02,286
Forget it. Our nonsense is
so much better than your nonsense.

200
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,625
Look at this guy!
He can be a Pixar hero.

201
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:05,750
Look at him!

202
00:09:05,836 --> 00:09:09,916
No, maybe I'm just not cut out
for the God game.

203
00:09:10,007 --> 00:09:12,297
Maybe I could teach S.A.T. Prep.

204
00:09:12,385 --> 00:09:15,845
At least there are answers
in the back of that book.

205
00:09:17,765 --> 00:09:20,095
(grunts)

206
00:09:20,184 --> 00:09:23,814
(cries) What kind of poison
do you serve to a guy

207
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:26,186
whose daughter hates his guts?

208
00:09:26,274 --> 00:09:29,194
Yeah. Try a Duff Numb.
No flavor, just alcohol.

209
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:30,697
(gulps)

210
00:09:30,778 --> 00:09:33,988
I need something that makes me
feel better in my heart.

211
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:35,663
Like firing a writer.

212
00:09:35,741 --> 00:09:37,871
Especially one who just bought a house.

213
00:09:37,952 --> 00:09:39,162
Mm...

214
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:40,575
(cash register dings)

215
00:09:40,663 --> 00:09:43,963
My son, I'm here to guide you
to the most powerful man

216
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:46,501
in this world, or any other.

217
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,336
J.J. Abrams?

218
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:50,171
No. Jesus.

219
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:53,506
He is reaching his arms out to you.

220
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:57,514
Oh, my God. I can see him.

221
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,427
I am a Christian!

222
00:09:59,515 --> 00:10:02,265
(angelic voices singing)

223
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:04,061
(stun gun crackling)

224
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:06,185
Uh, Chief, I think you got him.

225
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:07,822
Yeah, it's Christmas. (chuckles)

226
00:10:07,898 --> 00:10:10,858
Just bang his head on the car door
and we'll call it a day.

227
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:12,363
Merry Christmas.

228
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:14,445
Good night, sweet Maggie. Mwah.

229
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:18,199
Why are you huddling over there?
The gnome can't see you.

230
00:10:18,284 --> 00:10:20,204
I'll move your crib closer.

231
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,286
(grunting)

232
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:25,536
There.

233
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:29,126
(clock ticking)

234
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:34,433
Oh, sorry, I forgot your nightlight.

235
00:10:36,385 --> 00:10:38,715
(in baby voice)
The gnome can't nibble your fingers

236
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:40,394
if he can't see them.

237
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,813
<i>(Psycho </i>type violin stings)

238
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:47,401
Hey, Maggie.
I thought I'd try the violin.

239
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,570
<i>(Psycho </i>type violin stings)

240
00:10:51,150 --> 00:10:52,490
(wind whistling)

241
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:55,823
(object falls)

242
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:59,740
(wind whistling)

243
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:03,504
(terrified sucking)

244
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:08,081
I've got a tummy ache.

245
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:11,667
Maybe I ate too much before bedtime.

246
00:11:17,134 --> 00:11:19,894
Have you been a bad baby?

247
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:22,770
Oh. Don't lie to me...

248
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:25,888
