251
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:39,946
(laughs)

252
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:42,032
(yells)

253
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,293
Oh, don't worry, Maggie.

254
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:48,121
He can't beat
the super team of Santa,

255
00:11:48,207 --> 00:11:51,127
Jack Frost, the Abominable Snowman,

256
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:53,300
and Wayne Gretzky.

257
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:54,799
He's got a gun.

258
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:17,741
Merry Christmas, Maggie!

259
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:23,533
Was Maggie a good little girl?

260
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:25,367
She was?!

261
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:29,003
Well, you did such a good job, Mr. Gnome,

262
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:32,501
that we're gonna leave you here
all year round.

263
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:42,343
{\an8}("Joy to the World" instrumental playing)

264
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:46,178
"...which they also did
and sent to the elders

265
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,725
by the hands of Barnabas and Saul."

266
00:12:47,808 --> 00:12:49,518
Now, I'd like to introduce

267
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:52,152
our newest brother in faith--

268
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:54,059
Krusty the Christian.

269
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:57,568
<i>♪ Amazing grace ♪</i>

270
00:12:57,651 --> 00:13:00,991
<i>♪ How sweet the sound ♪</i>

271
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:04,331
<i>♪ That saved a putz ♪</i>

272
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:06,988
<i>♪ Like me ♪</i>

273
00:13:07,077 --> 00:13:11,167
<i>KRUSTY (thinking): Aw, I remember</i>
<i>the day she came into my life.</i>

274
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:18,005
Oh, here's a present for Maggie.

275
00:13:20,466 --> 00:13:23,086
And the good news is,
Spycraft Toys

276
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,927
makes other invasive dolls--

277
00:13:25,012 --> 00:13:27,312
Narc In The Park,
Bear Who's Always There,

278
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:28,889
and Snoop While You Poop.

279
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:31,814
Won't that be fun? So much fun.
(slurps)

280
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:40,319
Oh, now, sweetie,
that's a present for your mother.

281
00:13:40,402 --> 00:13:43,112
{\an8}(chuckles)
Another Christmas in the bag.

282
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:45,157
{\an8}I love my juicer.

283
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:50,079
{\an8}And don't worry, Marge, I'm adding fruit.

284
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:56,503
{\an8}You know, I might have
one more present for you.

285
00:13:58,462 --> 00:14:01,132
(chuckles excitedly)

286
00:14:02,132 --> 00:14:03,382
(both scream)

287
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:04,757
(scared stammering)

288
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:06,894
What is it? What is it?!

289
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:09,425
HOMER: What the...

290
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,555
(panting)

291
00:14:15,437 --> 00:14:16,687
(drumroll)

292
00:14:16,772 --> 00:14:21,282
<i>Welcome to the Krusty the Clown</i>
<i>Sober Contemplation Hour.</i>

293
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:24,200
-(cymbals crash)
-Pray, pray, kids.

294
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,780
We've got a very uplifting show today.

295
00:14:26,866 --> 00:14:27,986
He is risen.

296
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:29,655
And now please silently reflect

297
00:14:29,743 --> 00:14:33,753
upon the wholesome new teachings
of Itchy and Scratchy.

298
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:35,621
{\an8}<i>♪ They pray, they pray ♪</i>

299
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:37,668
{\an8}<i>♪ They pray and they don't slay ♪</i>

300
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:40,091
{\an8}<i>♪ Pray, pray, pray, they found a way ♪</i>

301
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:43,170
<i>♪ The pious mouse and cat ♪</i>

302
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:52,138
{\an8}"They shall beat their swords
into plowshares."

303
00:14:52,224 --> 00:14:55,144
{\an8}I think it's about time
we put on some clothes.

304
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:57,147
(both grunting)

305
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:59,769
And then this happened.

306
00:14:59,857 --> 00:15:02,527
Wow, Dad, you wrecked your entire show

307
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,320
just to prove you love me.

308
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:05,653
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

309
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:07,198
Here comes a cream pie.

310
00:15:07,281 --> 00:15:09,871
(pennywhistle plays)

311
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:12,540
-(Krusty chuckles softly)
-(Bart groans)

312
00:15:15,623 --> 00:15:19,503
Coming up next,
we've got some hilarious comedians.

313
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:20,625
Finally.

314
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:24,011
Andrew Nice Clay,
Larry the Fable Guy,

315
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:26,219
and Joe Piscopalian.

316
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:29,680
Oh, if he was gonna convert,
why didn't he pick a funny religion?

317
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:32,012
Like Zoroastrianism.

318
00:15:32,097 --> 00:15:34,057
Their top god is named Mazda.

319
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:36,891
-Tell me that's not hilarious.
-(groans)

320
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:40,107
And now the moment
you've been waiting for...

321
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:43,859
The nature of the universe
is we are forced to wait for every moment.

322
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,243
-As Mazda teaches us...
-Shh!

323
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:48,360
My daughter will play the French horn

324
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:51,277
and no one's pants will drop.

325
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:54,498
(plays upbeat melody)

326
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:58,670
I guess this will just be for me.

327
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:04,763
Well, look at you,
all cool and collected.

328
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:07,628
Oh, well, even the Lord rested on Sunday.

329
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:10,716
But Krusty's not ours
till he's b-b-b-baptized.

330
00:16:10,803 --> 00:16:14,893
You have to get his soul
and his bank router number on autopay.

331
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:17,734
Oh, he wanted to do it
the old-fashioned way,

332
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:20,600
in the river with Miss Teenage Nevada,

333
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:22,058
but the river's frozen.

334
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:23,857
I have to wait until the ice melts.

335
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:26,741
Mm-mm-mm.
I had you pegged for a closer, Tim.

336
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:29,909
You know, Ogdenville
is looking for a prison chaplain.

337
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:33,659
The last one, well,
he got a very cool tattoo...

338
00:16:33,742 --> 00:16:36,162
that he didn't ask for.

339
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:37,115
-(Helen gasps)
-(glass shatters)

340
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:39,004
(mouse squeaks)

341
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:41,081
<i>♪ Gather with the saints ♪</i>

342
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:43,836
<i>♪ At the river ♪</i>

343
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:49,259
<i>♪ That flows by the throne of God ♪</i>

344
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:52,011
<i>(squeaky-voice)</i>
<i>♪ Throne of God ♪</i>

345
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:57,144
Will the baptismal candidate
please approach?

346
00:16:57,224 --> 00:16:59,484
{\an8}-(laughing)
-(grunting)

347
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,270
{\an8}You're sure you want to do this, Dad?
Seems kind of meshugana.

348
00:17:02,354 --> 00:17:04,614
{\an8}I want to be a total Christian
for you, babe,

349
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:07,320
{\an8}so I'm gonna shpritz my tuchis...

350
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:08,941
{\an8}Be careful of the current.

351
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:11,528
{\an8}Don't worry,
I haven't been current in years.

352
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:14,493
{\an8}-(laughs boisterously, groans)
-(laughter)

353
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:18,080
(laughter continues)

354
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:24,289
Huh? Huh? Oh.

355
00:17:24,376 --> 00:17:28,506
Oh, great, my death is
a hacky parody of <i>Frozen.</i>

356
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:32,295
Dad? But who's the moose?

357
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:33,974
I'm your first agent.

358
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:36,643
Oh, this is the most we've ever spoken.

359
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:39,182
-(cell phone rings)
-(groans)

360
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:40,596
I must be dead.

361
00:17:40,684 --> 00:17:41,984
You're not dead yet.

362
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:43,981
Listen, I should know, because I am.

363
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:46,323
And life was no picnic,
but let me tell you,

364
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:47,978
death is no picnic, either.

365
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,687
Your biggest mistake
is expecting picnics.

366
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:51,858
Dad!

367
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:55,025
Oh, I suppose you're not happy
that I'm converting.

368
00:17:55,115 --> 00:17:58,365
Herschel, your heart just stopped,
so I'll make this very quick.

369
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:01,332
There's no one religion
that makes you a good father.

370
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,503
All you got to do
is think of your children

371
00:18:03,582 --> 00:18:05,332
before yourself, that's all...

372
00:18:05,417 --> 00:18:08,167
except with those oxygen masks
that you get on the planes.

373
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:09,843
There it's vice-a-versa.

374
00:18:09,922 --> 00:18:11,592
Well, I guess you would know.

375
00:18:11,673 --> 00:18:14,683
You're a rabbi
who's seen the face of God.

376
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,010
Actually, I'm a hallucination
caused by cell death

377
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:18,506
in your suffocating brain.

378
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:21,847
Also, I saw you texting
during my funeral.

379
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:24,444
-For shame!
-(cries out)

380
00:18:25,521 --> 00:18:28,021
Oh, reel him in.
You've caught a drowning man!

381
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:29,477
Slow down.

382
00:18:29,566 --> 00:18:31,316
First I'm gonna play him a little.

383
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:38,778
"I shall be a fisher of men."

384
00:18:42,621 --> 00:18:45,211
(ice breaking)

385
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:48,040
I'm alive! Oh, ho!

386
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:49,997
Don't tell my ex-wife.

387
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:53,046
(whooping and cheering)

388
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,552
Lovejoy is a hero!

389
00:18:55,634 --> 00:18:58,724
Finally, something I can explain!

390
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,974
{\an8}<i>SINGERS: ♪ All ended well</i>
<i>except for Sideshow Mel ♪</i>

391
00:19:01,056 --> 00:19:03,096
<i>♪ This Jewish clown, he didn't drown ♪</i>

392
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:05,393
<i>♪ Reconciled with his daughter ♪</i>

393
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:07,767
<i>♪ When he got out of the water ♪</i>

394
00:19:07,855 --> 00:19:09,975
<i>♪ Here's the good news,</i>
<i>butts in the pews ♪</i>

395
00:19:10,065 --> 00:19:12,065
<i>♪ Watch Homer snooze</i>
<i>as he still chews ♪</i>

396
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:15,071
{\an8}<i>♪ Our show is almost done,</i>
<i>Maggie didn't stop ♪</i>

397
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:17,824
{\an8}<i>♪ At one ♪</i>

398
00:19:23,453 --> 00:19:25,413
Sorry about Krusty,

399
00:19:25,497 --> 00:19:27,917
but he's still on Team Hanukkah.

400
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,590
Um, I hate to win on a technicality,

401
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,919
but he was under the water.

402
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,915
That's a baptism.

403
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:36,927
Maybe we should ask Mazda?

404
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,299
I'm not going to ask him anything,
he's drunk.

405
00:19:39,386 --> 00:19:41,926
(slurring) Oh, and like you're not!

406
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,854
(slurping)

407
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:51,435
♪ ♪

408
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:53,943
<i>♪ Just hear those sleigh bells jingling ♪</i>

409
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:56,606
<i>♪ Ring-ting-tingling along ♪</i>

410
00:19:56,695 --> 00:19:58,605
<i>♪ Let's sing a jolly holiday ♪</i>

411
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:01,987
<i>♪ Non-denominational song ♪</i>

412
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:04,825
<i>♪ Being pulled through the snow</i>
<i>to a wintertime feast ♪</i>

413
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:07,292
<i>♪ By a PVC beast ♪</i>

414
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:10,962
<i>♪ My website traffic just increased ♪</i>

415
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:12,963
<i>♪ Best get you home to your mother ♪</i>

416
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:15,755
<i>♪ Or she'll call a lawyer or two ♪</i>

417
00:20:15,839 --> 00:20:19,219
<i>♪ There's nothing better</i>
<i>than spending alternate weekends ♪</i>

418
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:21,971
<i>♪ With you ♪</i>

419
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:24,064
(theme music playing)

420
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:03,934
-(crowd murmuring)
-Shh!

421
00:21:04,012 --> 00:21:06,522
